<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The member 'arg' of OS_object_iter_t is declared as 'void *arg' but is only used as an input to the match callback and never modified (e.g. OS_ObjectIdIteratorGetNext calls iter->match(iter->arg, &iter->token, record) and there are no writes to *arg in the shown code). Therefore it can and should be declared as 'const void *arg' so the pointer points to a const-qualified type.
</scenario>
